CatDescriptText: Miss Betty Brown, 2081 South Court, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 31, 1958, pg. A1, question reads: "Do you think people follow political leadership more than religious leadership? Why?" Answer reads: "The minster does. I don't know why he does, but he does."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Betty Brown, wearing light colored trench coat, holding little boy wearing tweed coat and dark handbag, standing on corner of Fifth Avenue and Liberty Avenue in front of May Building with sign reading "Kappels", Downtown
